<TITLE> Ellen Goldstein new WB country chief </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 21 (bdnews24.com)The world Bank Group has named Ellen Goldstein as the new country manager in Bangladesh. Goldstein is due to take over responsibilities on Dec 9-10, the bank's public information officer in Dhaka office, Mehrin M Mahbub, told bdnews24.com. She carried out responsibility as country director of African Development Bank in countries of West regions of Africa and was country manager of WB for Burkina Faso for three years to 2007 Goldstein will replace Xian Zhu who left office in June. Robert L Floyd is currently the acting country manager. bd
